1.Create a New Branch & Push

git checkout -b branchname
git add .
git commit -m 
git pull
git push orgin branchname
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2.Raise a Pull Request (PR)

git push origin feature-branch
# then either:
gh pr create --base main --head feature-branch --title "Feature XYZ" --body "Details"
# or open GitHub UI â†’ "Compare & Pull Request"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. To avoid conflicts 

git pull origin main                # keep branch updated with latest main
# If conflicts occur:
# Fix conflicts manually in files â†’ then
git add <filename>                  # stage resolved files
git commit -m "Resolved conflicts"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. TO save the changes temporiarily 

git stash                           # save changes temporarily
git stash list                      # show stashes
git stash apply                     # bring changes back
git stash drop                      # delete stash

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5.TO close a PR 
gh pr close <PR_number> --delete-branch
--------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Delete a Branch 
git branch -d feature-branch        # delete branch locally (safe delete)
git branch -D feature-branch        # force delete locally
git push origin --delete feature-branch   # delete branch from remote
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Keep your feature branch updated with the latest main:

git checkout feature-branch
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ“˜ Git Study Notes â€“ Important Daily Scenarios
ðŸŸ¦ 1. Creating & Managing Branches
Create a new branch
git checkout -b feature-branch

Switch to an existing branch
git checkout branch-name

List branches
git branch

ðŸŸ© 2. Adding & Committing Changes
Stage all changes
git add .

Stage a specific file
git add filename

Commit changes
git commit -m "Meaningful commit message"

ðŸŸ§ 3. Pushing Code to Remote
Push a new branch to remote
git push origin feature-branch

Push latest commits
git push

ðŸŸª 4. Raising a Pull Request (PR)
Using GitHub CLI
gh pr create --base main --head feature-branch \
  --title "Feature Title" \
  --body "Feature Description"

Using GitHub UI

Go to repo â†’ Compare & Pull Request â†’ Create PR

ðŸŸ¥ 5. Keeping Branch Updated (Avoid Conflicts)
Best practice (Rebase with Main)
git checkout feature-branch
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main

Alternative (Merge main into your branch)
git pull origin main

ðŸŸ« 6. Resolving Merge Conflicts
Fix conflicts manually â†’ then stage:
git add <filename>

Continue rebase/merge
git rebase --continue

Abort rebase if too messy
git rebase --abort

After rebase, push (force needed)
git push origin feature-branch --force

ðŸŸ¨ 7. Merging PR into Main/Master
Most common (UI merge)

Click Merge Pull Request â†’ choose:

Squash & Merge

Merge Commit

Rebase & Merge

Using Git CLI (if allowed)
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge feature-branch
git push origin main

ðŸŸ« 8. Closing or Deleting a PR
Close a PR
gh pr close <PR_number>

Close PR + delete branch
gh pr close <PR_number> --delete-branch

ðŸŸ¤ 9. Deleting Branches
Delete local branch
git branch -d feature-branch
git branch -D feature-branch

Delete remote branch
git push origin --delete feature-branch

ðŸŸ© 10. Git Stash (Temporary Save)
git stash
git stash list
git stash apply
git stash pop
git stash drop

ðŸŸ¦ 11. Git Status
git status

ðŸŸ§ 12. Deleting Files in Git
git rm filename
git commit -m "Removed filename"
git push

ðŸŸª 13. Undoing Changes
Undo last commit (keep your changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

Discard changes in a file
git checkout -- filename

ðŸŸ« 14. Viewing Commit History
git log --oneline --graph --decorate

ðŸŸ© 15. Daily Workflow Summary
1. Create branch
git checkout -b feature-branch

2. Develop â†’ Stage â†’ Commit
git add .
git commit -m "message"

3. Push to remote
git push origin feature-branch

4. Raise PR
5. Rebase regularly (avoid conflicts)
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main
git push --force

6. Merge PR
7. Delete branch
git branch -d feature-branch
git push origin --delete feature-branch




